Eternal Valor</font><P> <P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urewena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rewena</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>RTA WebAdmin</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>337</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2/27/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11:25:12 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Indy day questions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">An indy day is just a day taken off the regular calendar. It is a day set aside for all those that are not currently members of posting entities.<br>
<br>
As far as the calendar, it's admins, and the guilds/alliances that currently use it more or less this day simply doesn't exist.<br>
<br>
The exception to this is if a god is up. On the regular calendar there is a system for making sure the god dies if the guild/alliance that has the plane reserved can not take him down. However the guild/alliance that reserved the day does get the chance to try first. This is what also happens on indy days. You have until midnight to kill the god. If at that time he is still alive the 6 epics guilds are free to zone in and make sure he dies.<br>
<br>
So to answer your question this means that you get the chance to kill the god and finish your epic =) However if you can't do it by midnight then you may lose the opportunity. <br>
<br>
Good luck on your raid =)</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umilambus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milambus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Noble Blade</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>198</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>2/27/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11:25:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Indy day questions</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The rules for Indy Days are pretty easy.<br>
<br>
- Anyone not in a posting entity can go in the plane.  (Really they can up at anytime on anyday but doing so will cause bad will with posting entities.)<br>
<br>
- If the god is still up at 12am PST, a BB guild can come in and take him down.  (Probably the current BB guild)<br>
<br>
If you kill the god before 12am PST, good.  That rule is just there for the chance the god would still be alive.  Because by definitation there is no ONE person to call in a BB guild for a god, a time limit was put into place instead.<br>
<br>
